    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Temporal Bones safe for kids?",
        "answer": "Yes. The scan uses no radiation, and our technologists are trained in paediatric sedation and distraction techniques.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon will I get results?",
        "answer": "Most reports are available the same evening. Critical findings are phoned to your doctor within 30 minutes.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need contrast every time?",
        "answer": "No. A non-contrast scan is often enough. Contrast is added only when infection, tumor, or nerve inflammation is suspected.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive after the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you received sedation. In that case, arrange a companion for 4–6 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I'm claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "We offer an open-bore MRI, music headphones, and mild oral sedation on request.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " Are there any side effects from the MRI scan?",
        "answer": "MRI is considered very safe with no known long-term side effects. The most common issues are related to claustrophobia or, very rarely, a mild allergic reaction to the contrast agent. Our team at Cadabam's Diagnostics is fully prepared to manage any such concerns.\n\nIf you have more questions about your upcoming scan, please don't hesitate to reach out to our team. For a comprehensive overview of our imaging services."
      }
    ],
